<collectingCountry box="[918,1026,1602,1623]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="4" pageNumber="25">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[1079,1155,1602,1623]" name="Panama" pageId="4" pageNumber="25">Panama</collectingCountry>
are 2.95 and 
<quantity box="[804,893,1629,1650]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.9" pageId="4" pageNumber="25" unit="mm" value="2.9">2.90 mm</quantity>
in length, respectively. Setae on the elytra of the Costa Rican specimen are pale gold in coloration, and the elytral surface beneath them has faint golden reflections.
</paragraph>
